{
  "name": "RPlog_The_Sin_of_a_Selas",
  "title": "The Sin of a Selas",
  "summary": "Aboard a starship hurtling through space, the Selas wanderer Simon Sezirok drifts into the quiet medbay where the comatose fallen Jedi Jessalyn Valios lies, freshly recovered from a stasis tomb. Drawn to her despite himself, Simon wrestles with a forbidden temptation: to reach through the True Source -- the Force -- into her bottled, strangely lucid consciousness and try to heal her imperiled soul, an act his people consider the gravest of sins. Twice he centers himself and probes her mind, glimpsing her memories of Sith, Emperor Valak, the Rebellion's heroes, and above all her master Luke Skywalker, whose visage collides violently with Simon's own hatred of the Jedi and throws him from his chair. Pressing on, Simon manages to send a thought of his name and intent across the barrier and brushes her contentment, stirring only confusion before recoiling in anguish. He weeps, certain he has violated this stranger and lost his innocence in a way he can never forgive.",
